<h1 align="center">Counselling on assembler tasks.</h1>

<p>Bixoft may well counsel you or your team on all possible activities
 in the
 area of assembler. More details can be found under each of the topics
 in the
 right-hand column at the bottom of this page.</p>

<p>Counselling may amongst others include the following:</p>
<ul>
 <li>Transfer of knowledge.<br />
  For more information please refer to the topic
  '<a href="courses.htm">Courses</a>'.<br />
  If required we will gladly compile a course that will address your
  specific
  requirements.<br />
  &nbsp;<br /></li>
 <li>Supervision.<br />
  Professional and technical leadership to a team of programmers.
 <br />
  &nbsp;<br /></li>
 <li>Walkthroughs and reviews.<br />
  When doing a walkthrough we check the design or code (pro-actively),
  to see
  where it might be improved. When reviewing we look back (reactively)
  where
  things have gone awry, and how we may avoid these problems in the
  future.<br />
  &nbsp;<br /></li>
 <li>Assistance.<br />
  Actually assisting you to realize your project.<br />
  More details can be found under each of the topics in the right
  column
  at the bottom of this page.<br />
  &nbsp;<br /></li>
 <li>Soundboard-function.<br />
  Brainstorming together about the design, help to find alternative
  solutions,
  etc.<br />
  &nbsp;<br /></li>
 <li>Source of information.<br />
  For all your questions in the area of assembler. By phone, by
  e-mail, or in a
  meeting either at your office, or at ours.</li>
</ul>

/HTML

